{
  "title": "New Renderings Revealed For Fulton Bond",
  "content": "<div><div class=\"entry-content e-content clearfix\"><p>New renderings have been revealed for the multi-tower Fulton Bond development at 1325 West Fulton Street in the <a href=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/category/fulton-market\">Fulton Market District</a>. Bound by North Ada Street to the west and North Elizabeth Street to the east, the block-long development was originally revealed in late 2024 and has <a href=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/2025/07/outer-shell-complete-for-1325-west-fulton-sales-center-in-fulton-market-district.html\">recently completed</a> its on-site sales center as the team prepares to begin selling units.</p><div id=\"attachment_71997\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-1024x520.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" class=\"size-large wp-image-71997\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-1024x520.jpg 1024w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-300x152.jpg 300w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-768x390.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-1536x779.jpg 1536w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-2048x1039.jpg 2048w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-777x394.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-260x132.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-591x300.jpg 591w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-310x157.jpg 310w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1325-W-Fulton-Street-01-150x76.jpg 150w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Site map of 1325 W Fulton Street by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><div id=\"attachment_88051\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-1024x480.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" class=\"size-large wp-image-88051\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-1024x480.jpg 1024w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-300x141.jpg 300w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-768x360.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-1536x720.jpg 1536w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-2048x960.jpg 2048w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-777x364.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-260x122.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-640x300.jpg 640w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-310x145.jpg 310w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-12-150x70.jpg 150w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">PREVIOUS (left) – current (right) renderings of Fulton Bond by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><p>Efforts for the project are being led by Sulo Development, which has been working with architecture firms KPF and ParkFowler Plus on the design. The original plans called for three separate phases, each with its own tower and a portion of an eventual site-wide podium. The project <a href=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/2025/02/city-council-approves-condo-towers-in-fulton-market.html\">received city approval</a> in early 2025.</p><div id=\"attachment_88048\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-1024x726.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" class=\"size-large wp-image-88048\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-1024x726.jpg 1024w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-300x213.jpg 300w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-768x544.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-1536x1088.jpg 1536w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-2048x1451.jpg 2048w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-777x551.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-260x184.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-423x300.jpg 423w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-310x220.jpg 310w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-03-148x105.jpg 148w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rendering of Fulton Bond by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><p>The original first phase was to be anchored by a 29-story tower reaching 438 feet and containing 80 condos. This would be followed by a 19-story middle tower with 50 units, and eventually a 39-story tower with 110 units reaching 540 feet in height. However, the project’s Instagram account posted a new rendering this week focusing on just two towers with a slightly altered design.</p><div id=\"attachment_88047\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" class=\"size-large wp-image-88047\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-300x200.jpg 300w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-768x511.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-1536x1023.jpg 1536w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-2048x1363.jpg 2048w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-777x517.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-260x173.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-451x300.jpg 451w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-310x206.jpg 310w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-04-150x100.jpg 150w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rendering of Fulton Bond by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><div id=\"attachment_88046\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-1024x684.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" class=\"size-large wp-image-88046\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-300x200.jpg 300w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-768x513.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-777x519.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-260x174.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-449x300.jpg 449w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-310x207.jpg 310w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-05-150x100.jpg 150w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rendering of Fulton Bond by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><p>The project will still commence on the eastern end of the site, though the first phase will now stand around 25 stories tall. Its massing has been slightly simplified, with the crown completely redesigned to feature a corrugated covering. While the lower levels have retained their rounded brick arches, the balconies no longer carry that same detailing. It is unclear whether this revision will impact the unit count.</p><div id=\"attachment_88044\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-846x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"846\" class=\"size-large wp-image-88044\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-846x1024.jpg 846w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-248x300.jpg 248w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-768x929.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-1270x1536.jpg 1270w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-1693x2048.jpg 1693w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-777x940.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-260x315.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-256x310.jpg 256w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-07-87x105.jpg 87w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rendering of Fulton Bond by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><p>To the west, a small motor court will remain next to a completely revised second phase. This tower will now become the tallest in the development, rising 33 stories and approximately 500 feet. It will take on a similar massing to the first tower but will be clad in dark gray brick, sharing the podium constructed during the first phase. This tower will likely contain around 100 units.</p><div id=\"attachment_88045\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-1024x678.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" class=\"size-large wp-image-88045\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-1024x678.jpg 1024w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-300x199.jpg 300w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-768x508.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-1536x1017.jpg 1536w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-2048x1356.jpg 2048w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-777x514.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-260x172.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-453x300.jpg 453w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-310x205.jpg 310w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-06-150x99.jpg 150w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rendering of Fulton Bond by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><div id=\"attachment_88049\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-1024x711.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" class=\"size-large wp-image-88049\" srcset=\"https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-1024x711.jpg 1024w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-300x208.jpg 300w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-768x533.jpg 768w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-1536x1067.jpg 1536w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-2048x1422.jpg 2048w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-777x540.jpg 777w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-260x181.jpg 260w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-432x300.jpg 432w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-310x215.jpg 310w, https://chicagoyimby.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Fulton-Bond-02-150x105.jpg 150w\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rendering of Fulton Bond by KPF and ParkFowler Plus</p></div><p>While not much else is known, the interiors are expected to feature high-end finishes and amenities. The rendering also shows open space to the west of the central tower, which could be reserved for an eventual third phase. It is unclear why these changes were made, but the team is set to begin sales in the coming months and break ground on the first phase shortly thereafter.</p><p> <a href=\"http://eepurl.com/g_VSUf\"><strong>Subscribe</strong></a> to YIMBY’s daily e-mail<br> <br> <a href=\"https://instagram.com/yimbygram\"><strong>Follow</strong></a> YIMBYgram for real-time photo updates<br> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/YIMBYFB\"><strong>Like</strong></a>&nbsp;YIMBY on Facebook<br> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/yimbytweets\"><strong>Follow</strong></a> YIMBY’s Twitter for the latest in YIMBYnews</p></div></div>",
